Class PartManager<O extends PartOwner,P extends PartManager.Part<O>>

        • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.model.far.PartManager<O,P>
  • Type Parameters:
    O - type of owner
    P - type of part.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Contexed, ContextCached, FormCreatorProducer, FormUpdateProducer<P>, FilterMatcher<P>, TypeConverter<P,java.lang.Number>, Selector<DataObjectItemInput<P>>, Owner, IndexedProducer<P>, Tagged, Targetted<P>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    HandlerPartManager, PageManager

    public abstract class PartManager<O extends PartOwner,P extends PartManager.Part<O>>
extends PartOwnerFactory<P>
    abstract super-class for a part or sub-part of a Form. There may be several levels in the hierarchy so parts also implement PartOwner

    Each part references its parent, has an order field that determines the order of parts within the parent and has a name field that is unique within the parent.

    The factory classes are expected to always be referenced via their parent and their identifying tags are derived from the parent tags so that if multiple tables of forms are created they automatically generate independent tables of parts this makes it easier to remove entire classes of form.

    Author:
    spb
